{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3732676,"name":"Kyle Burman","username":"Flatop","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/f/a4c791/{size}.png","created_at":"2025-09-06T19:23:45.167Z","cooked":"<p>We have been trying to get our Swerve Pose Estimator working for a while, but we have run into a few roadblocks. For whatever reason, if our wheels are pointing in the opposite direction than our code is expecting, for example, the wheels are pointed 180 degrees instead of 0 degrees. Also, if we use the</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">SwerveModuleState state = SwerveModuleState.optimize(desiredState, new Rotation2d(encoderValue())); 
</code></pre>
<p>function, then our pose estimation will go the same way whether or not we go forward or backward. This causes problems when we have tried using the command drive to location  that we have written ourselves using the pose estimator for positioning. We use the relative encoder that is on our NEOs for driving, with Thrifty top encoders for turning.</p>
